oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Two real photo postcards of the 30th Div. return
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: These two real photo post cards show slightly different view of soldiers marching in the Celebration Day parade of the 30th Div. on their return to Chattanooga, Tenn. on April 3, 1919. The 30th Division was composed of National Guard units from Tennessee, North Carolina, and South Carolina. The Division was organized at Camp Sevier, South Carolina and served with the British army in World War, 1917-1918. Many Tennesseans served in the 30th Division.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: World War, 1914-1918; World War, 1914-1918 - History
